<div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
  <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl text-stone-900 mb-6">About Specimen Gallery</h1>

  <p class="text-lg text-stone-600 mb-10 leading-relaxed">
    Specimen Gallery is an open-source collection of high-quality, transparent-background images of natural specimens. It exists to provide researchers, educators, illustrators, and students with freely usable specimen cutouts for scientific and educational purposes.
  </p>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 mb-4">How uploads work</h2>
    <ol class="space-y-3 text-stone-600">
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium flex items-center justify-center">1</span>
        <span>Upload a specimen image (PNG, WebP, or JPG/HEIC with background removal)</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium flex items-center justify-center">2</span>
        <span>Enter the scientific name — suggestions from GBIF help validate taxonomy</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium flex items-center justify-center">3</span>
        <span>Optionally enable automatic background removal to generate a transparent PNG</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium flex items-center justify-center">4</span>
        <span>Submission is reviewed for quality and basic correctness</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium flex items-center justify-center">5</span>
        <span>Once approved, your specimen appears in the gallery</span>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 mb-4">Licensing</h2>
    <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Contributors choose how their images can be used:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-3 text-stone-600">
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 font-mono text-sm bg-stone-200 px-2 py-1 rounded">CC0</span>
        <span>Public domain. Free to use for any purpose, no attribution required.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-3">
        <span class="flex-shrink-0 font-mono text-sm bg-stone-200 px-2 py-1 rounded">CC-BY</span>
        <span>Free to use, but you must credit the contributor.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-stone-800 mb-4">Quality guidelines</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-stone-600">
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600">•</span>
        <span>Clear specimen image with minimal artifacts or background remnants</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600">•</span>
        <span>Accurate scientific name if known — uncertain names are flagged for review</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600">•</span>
        <span>No copyrighted images unless you own the rights and the license permits</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex gap-2">
        <span class="text-amber-600">•</span>
        <span>No sensitive, illegal, or inappropriate content</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <div class="pt-6 border-t border-stone-200">
    <p class="text-sm text-stone-500">
      Questions? See our <%= link_to "Terms", terms_path, class: "text-amber-600 hover:underline" %> or contact us.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

